radiographic_examinations.findings: Long T2 signals near the anterior horns and bodies of bilateral lateral ventricles indicating subependymal cysts, and widened bilateral posterior horns of lateral ventricles.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: The abnormalities persisted and were more pronounced as the pregnancy progressed.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild patent ductus arteriosus, patent foramen ovale, and mitral and tricuspid regurgitation.
